gomodel:SYNGO_5096  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: muskelin (MKLN1) is partially localized to the postsynaptic sites of inhibitory synapses (but also at e.g. nonsynaptic intracellular vesicles) and can interact with GABAARα1 (GABRA1).\n\nFigure 3: Muskelin depletion causes increased GABAARα1 surface levels with accumulation at extrasynaptic sites.\n\nFigure 4: Muskelin-myosinVI (MYO6) interactions facilitate F-actin dependent GABAARα1 internalization in WT but not in muskelin and myosinVI mutant mice.\n\nFigure 6: Dynein-driven, retrograde transport complex containing muskelin and GABAAR α1.\n\nFigure 7: Muskelin is co-localized with GABAARα1 at (late) endosomes and facilitates degradation of GABAARα1.\n\nAuthors summarize:\n\"our data demonstrate that muskelin acts as a dual component with common functions in two subsequent internalization and degradation steps involving different cytoskeletal elements and motor proteins (Figure 8).\". Experimental description: suppl. M&M: \"Electron Microscopy - Preembedding immunohistochemistry: mice were anaesthetized and perfused with ...\"\n\nantibody:\nguinea pig anti Muskelin (Tagnaouti et al., 2007, PMID:17474996)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5096" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

